## SERVER 2 — STRIPE MCP (Diagnostic Only)

Connected with read-only tools only — cannot charge cards or modify subscriptions.

### When to call Stripe MCP

| Symptom | MCP Tool to Call |
|---|---|
| Webhook not receiving events | `webhooks.read` → check endpoint exists + recent deliveries |
| Payment succeeded but DB not updated | `charges.read` → verify charge + check metadata.user_id |
| Subscription status wrong | `subscriptions.read` → read actual status |
| "No such customer" error | `customers.read` → verify customer exists in this mode |
| "No such price" error | `prices.read` → verify price ID exists in current environment |

### Available tools (read-only subset — stays under 40-tool limit)
- `customers.read` — look up customer by email or ID
- `subscriptions.read` / `subscriptions.search` — check subscription status
- `charges.read` — verify payment and metadata
- `payment_intents.read` — check payment intent status
- `webhooks.read` — list endpoints + recent delivery logs
- `products.read` / `prices.read` — verify product/price exists

### Key Stripe diagnostic: check webhook deliveries
When a webhook is suspected broken, use `webhooks.read` to see:
- Does the endpoint exist?
- What events is it subscribed to?
- What do the last 10 delivery attempts show?
This replaces manual checking in the Stripe dashboard entirely.

